SIMPLE: unfeeling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unfeeling
<hw>Un*feel"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Destitute of feeling; void of sensibility; insensible;
insensate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Without kind feelings; cruel;
hard-hearted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To each his sufferings: all are men,⟦br⟧
Condemned alike to groan;⟦br⟧
The tender for another's pain,⟦br⟧
Th' <qex>unfeeling</qex> for his own.</q> <rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*feel"ing*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*feel"ing*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unfeigned</ent>⟦br⟧
